This paper deals with Neural Machine Translation (NMT) using a linguistic resource, Interlinear Glossed Text (IGT), which is a natural language processing (NLP) task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves training a multilingual NMT model, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of shared attention across multiple languages suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Learning). The paper also involves low-resource machine translation, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with linguistic resources for multiple languages, which suggests the sub-category cs.CY (Computational Linguistics).
